Cooking Rice and Stew
For Rice
1 cup of white rice
2 cups of water
pinch of salt

For Stew 
1b(about 450g) of your preferred meat
1 onion,finely chopped
2 cloves of garlic, minced
1 can(14 0z/400g) of diced tomatoes
2 carrots, sliced
1 bell pepper, chopped
2 tablespoons of cooking oil
1 teaspoon of dried thyme
1 teaspoon of paprika
Salt and pepper to taste


Instructions
1. Rinse the rice under cold water until the water runs clear. In a pot, combine rice, water and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat , cover and simmer until the rice is cooked and water is absorbed.
2. In a separate pan, heat cooking oil over medium heat. Add chopped onions and minced garlic, saute until softened.
3. Add diced meat to the pan and cook until browned.
4. Stir in diced tomatoes, carrots and bell pepper. Season with thyme, paprika, salt and pepper. Simmer until the vegetables are tender and the flavors meld.
5. Once the rice is cooked, fluff it with a fork and serve alongside the stew.

